al CT\nquasar NGC6240 which is currently undergoing a major merger coupled with strong\nstar-formation. For typical X-ray bolometric correction factors, the accretion\nluminosity of Mrk34 is high enough to potentially power the total infrared\nluminosity. X-ray spectral fitting also shows that thermal emission related to\nstar-formation is unlikely to drive the observed bright soft component below ~3\nkeV, favoring photionization instead.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Jul 2014 20:00:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
